title: Police Searching For Woman After Mitchell House Fire
text:
Police Searching For Woman After Mitchell House Fire October 8, 2015, 1:41 PM Courtesy: uShare MITCHELL, SD - 
Mitchell authorities are searching for a person of interest after a Thursday morning house fire. 
At 8 a.m. Thursday, authorities were called to 800 E. 7th Ave. for a house fire. Police said the home was unoccupied at the time. 
The Mitchell Department of Public Safety is looking for 37-year-old Dawn Elizabeth Long, the only resident to not be accounted for. 
Authorities think Long is in the Rapid City area, and may have her two dogs. She is described as a white female, 5'7" tall and weighs 160 pounds with green eyes. She may be driving a gray 2014 Ford Escape with South Dakota license plates 8B582. 
If you have any information, contact local law enforcement, or the Mitchell Police at 605-995-8400. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
